@*
    APP.RAZOR — Blazor Concept: Router Component (Application Root)

    React equivalent: App.tsx with <BrowserRouter> + <Routes> + <Route>
    Angular equivalent: app.routes.ts (route definitions) + RouterOutlet

    Key Blazor concepts:
    1. <Router> — Blazor's client-side router
       Scans the assembly for @page directives and builds a route table.
       React uses <BrowserRouter> + <Route path="...">;
       Angular uses provideRouter(routes) + <router-outlet>.

    2. AppAssembly — Tells the router which assembly to scan for @page routes
       @typeof(App).Assembly = "scan this project for routable components"
       React: You define routes explicitly in App.tsx
       Angular: You define routes in app.routes.ts

    3. <Found> / <NotFound> — Route match handling
       <Found> renders when a route matches (shows the page in a layout)
       <NotFound> renders when no @page directive matches the URL
       React equivalent: <Route path="*" element={<NotFound />} />

    4. DefaultLayout — Wraps all pages in MainLayout
       React equivalent: <Route element={<MainLayout />}> as a parent route
       Angular equivalent: AppComponent template with <router-outlet>

    5. RouteView — Renders the matched page component
       RouteData carries the matched component + parameters
       React equivalent: The element prop on <Route> renders the component

    NOTE: Unlike React/Angular where you define routes in a central file,
    Blazor discovers routes automatically from @page directives in .razor files.
    No route registration needed — just add @page "/path" to any component!
*@
<Router AppAssembly="@typeof(App).Assembly">
    <Found Context="routeData">
        <RouteView RouteData="@routeData" DefaultLayout="@typeof(MainLayout)" />
        <FocusOnNavigate RouteData="@routeData" Selector="h1" />
    </Found>
    <NotFound>
        <PageTitle>Not found</PageTitle>
        <LayoutView Layout="@typeof(MainLayout)">
            <p role="alert">Sorry, there's nothing at this address.</p>
        </LayoutView>
    </NotFound>
</Router>
